00:00:02,260 --> 00:00:03,610
我是黛比・韦弗
My name is Debbie Weaver.

2
00:00:03,630 --> 00:00:04,850
这是我的家人
This is my family.

3
00:00:04,870 --> 00:00:07,170
这是我们过去在新泽西贝永的家
This is our old apartment in Bayonne, New Jersey.

4
00:00:07,190 --> 00:00:09,870
我丈夫马蒂在镇上给我们找了一个新房子
My husband Marty got us a deal on a town house...

5
00:00:09,890 --> 00:00:12,090
邻居和蔼 街道宽阔
nicer neighborhood, wider streets.

6
00:00:12,110 --> 00:00:13,860
只有一个小小的问题
Just one little problem...

7
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:16,090
我们的邻居全部来自另一个星球
our neighbors are all from another planet...

8
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:17,700
这不是玩笑
Literally.

9
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:20,200
姜饼人

10
00:00:20,260 --> 00:00:22,260
伯克小学

11
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:25,640
马蒂看啊
Look at this, Marty.

12
00:00:25,660 --> 00:00:28,070
我们在这可以做很多事
There's so much to volunteer for.

13
00:00:28,140 --> 00:00:30,090
在这里我们也许真的可以做些有意义的事呢
We could make a real difference at this school.

14
00:00:30,180 --> 00:00:32,970
这真无聊 人类真是无趣 
This is boring. Humans are boring.

15
00:00:33,630 --> 00:00:35,320
拉里・伯德太淡定了
Larry Bird is underwhelmed.

16
00:00:35,340 --> 00:00:37,200
那你怎么不找点有趣的事去做?
Well, why don't you find something that interests you?

17
00:00:37,220 --> 00:00:39,890
比如 我们准备参加家长教师联谊会
Yeah, like, I think we're gonna join the P.T.A.

18
00:00:40,980 --> 00:00:41,660
你想说啥?
What? What was that?

19
00:00:41,660 --> 00:00:43,020
不好说 家教会?
I don't know. The P.T.A.?

20
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:45,870
也许今年我们可以尝试下别的事情
I mean, maybe this year we should volunteer for different things.

21
00:00:45,890 --> 00:00:47,860
我可以去教足球
You know? I could coach soccer.

22
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:49,480
噢 当教练
Oh, coaching.

23
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:50,620
好吧 你有意见? 
Okay, what was that?

24
00:00:50,620 --> 00:00:51,940
我喜欢你做教练 好喜欢
I love when you coach. Love it.

25
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:53,700
是你说要做点有意义的事情
Well, you talk about making a difference.

26
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,060
做教练很有意义
Well, coaching is it.

27
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:56,960
还有什么比运动
What's better than molding young minds

28
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:58,700
更能磨练孩子们的意志 是吧?
through organized athletics, right?

29
00:00:58,720 --> 00:01:01,270
- 噢 听起来不错 - 马蒂 拜托
- Oh, that sounds interesting. - Come on, Marty.

30
00:01:01,290 --> 00:01:03,230
只不过就是你一边吹哨子 孩子们一边
It's you blowing a whistle while a bunch of kids

31
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:05,730
像一群疯牛一样在球场上乱跑
run across a field like a herd of confused cattle.

32
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:07,450
你当他们是曼联队啊
It's hardly Manchester United.

33
00:01:07,470 --> 00:01:09,890
家长教师协会又是做什么的?
What does this, uh, P.T.A. do exactly?

34
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:11,400
- 帮助学校... - 点心义卖
- It helps the school... - Bake sales.

35
00:01:11,420 --> 00:01:13,800
点心义卖只是其中一个很小的部分
Bake sales are a small part of it.

36
00:01:13,820 --> 00:01:16,600
可以借此开展文化项目
It's also a chance to install an arts program.

37
00:01:16,620 --> 00:01:19,160
是啊 之后就是你争我吵 勾心斗角
Yeah, and get mired in bickering and petty politics.

38
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:22,580
你争我吵 勾心斗角? 听上去真不错
Bickering and petty politics? Oh, that sounds delightful.

39
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:24,680
就像察布隆伊恩的议会
Just like zabvronian council.

40
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:28,930
夫人 我和黛比・韦弗去参加家长教师联谊会
Wife, I think I will join Debbie Weaver on this T.P.A.,

41
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:30,950
而你可以和马蒂教孩子们踢球 
and you can coach soccer with Marty.

42
00:01:30,950 --> 00:01:31,960
噢 太好了!
Oh, excellent!

43
00:01:31,980 --> 00:01:34,310
等会儿 你对运动了解吗?
Now hold on. Do you even know anything about sports?

44
00:01:34,330 --> 00:01:36,820
当然 小时候我并不是很出众
Oh, yes. I was nothing exceptional as a child,

45
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:39,790
但体育极大地补足了我的自信
but sports gave me some much-needed self-esteem.

46
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:43,220
真希望我们的小迪克也能像我一样
I was hoping that our little Dick might follow in my footsteps.

47
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:45,140
你为啥和我过不去?
Why are you fighting me?

48
00:01:51,490 --> 00:01:53,760
保重 教练
Good luck, coach.

49
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,950
呃 都是陈词滥调
Well, this is boilerplate stuff.

50
00:02:01,970 --> 00:02:05,290
你说察布隆伊恩的议会也兴这一套?
You say this is similar to your Zabvronian council?

51
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,920
那你应该能很快适应这儿
You should have no trouble keeping up.

52
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,640
你们的"希望屠夫"呢?
Where's your butcher of hope?

53
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:11,870
高个子 戴着黑色兜帽 来隐藏他无尽的悲伤
Tall chap, wears a dark hood to mask his eternal sorrow.

54
00:02:11,890 --> 00:02:13,950
所有争论的终结者
Puts an end to debates.

55
00:02:13,970 --> 00:02:17,220
没有他 会议怎么能正常进行?
How can you have a proper meeting without a butcher of hope?

56
00:02:17,740 --> 00:02:19,410
也许先跳过这项
Maybe skim this.

57
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:23,600
下一项议程是 点心义卖 筹资买新球服
The next item on the agenda is the bake sale for the new soccer uniforms.

58
00:02:23,620 --> 00:02:25,840
经过深思熟虑
Now, after giving it a lot of thought,

59
00:02:25,860 --> 00:02:27,590
我决定卖巧克力饼
I've decided we'll sell brownies.

60
00:02:27,610 --> 00:02:28,480
都同意是吗?
All in favor?

61
00:02:28,510 --> 00:02:31,850
打搅一下 我叫黛比・韦弗
Ooh! Excuse me. I'm Debbie Weaver,

62
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:34,570
- 马克斯和艾比的妈妈 - 你好黛比
- Max and Abby's mom. - Hello, Debbie.

63
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,650
虽然我不认识你的孩子 但你肯定告诉过他们
I don't know your children, but I'm sure you've taught them

64
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:38,710
打断别人说话是很失礼的
how rude it is to interrupt someone.

65
00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:40,840
哦 呵呵
Oh. Fun.

66
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:43,960
好的 我有个想法
Well, uh, okay. I have a couple of ideas.

67
00:02:44,270 --> 00:02:45,860
原来在贝永的学校
Back at our old school in Bayonne,

68
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,940
我们都用姜饼作主打
we made gingerbread cookies for the bake sale,

69
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:51,420
姜饼做成球队的形状
and we decorated them like the soccer team,

70
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,470
很受孩子们欢迎
and the kids loved 'em.

71
00:02:52,490 --> 00:02:54,680
所以每次都能赚到很多...
And we ended up making a lot of m...

72
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,170
钱
Money.

73
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:57,620
我们做了...
We made...

74
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:58,760
很多...
it was a lot of...

75
00:02:58,790 --> 00:03:01,930
姜饼... 都很好吃
They were... delicious.

76
00:03:02,380 --> 00:03:04,920
原来主席就是你们的"希望屠夫"
The president has become your butcher of hope.

77
00:03:04,940 --> 00:03:06,820
- 这可不是好兆头 - 闭嘴!
- Nothing good can come of this. - Just zip it!

78
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,980
谢谢你 黛比
Thank you, Debbie.

79
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,610
在贝永 你们能就地取材做点心
I'm sure in Bayonne, you used what you had,

80
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:13,770
我很佩服 但这里的情况不同
and I admire that, but we have different standards here.

81
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:15,840
所以还是做巧克力饼吧
So we'll be making brownies.

82
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:18,680
太不讲理了! 马蒂是对的
This is ridiculous! Marty was right.

83
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:20,950
家教会果然尽是勾心斗角 我们走
The P.T.A. Is just petty politics. Let's go.

84
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,920
不能善罢甘休
We shall do no such thing.

85
00:03:22,950 --> 00:03:24,950
这女人不仅否定你的观点
This woman is not only attacking your idea,

86
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,290
还否定了你 你的生活方式和你的孩子
she's attacking your very being, your way of life, your children.

87
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,170
她只是喜欢巧克力饼罢了
I think she just likes brownies.

88
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,960
抱歉
Excuse me.

89
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:34,460
协会手册规定
According to your guidelines,

90
00:03:34,510 --> 00:03:36,640
与筹资相关的任何议程
any decisions regarding fund-raising

91
00:03:36,660 --> 00:03:39,120
需由全体人员投票表决
must be voted upon by the entire group.

92
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:42,020
因此 我动议 通过投票... 
Therefore, I move we vote...

93
00:03:42,220 --> 00:03:44,810
来决定是卖姜饼还是巧克力饼
gingerbread men or brownies?

94
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,880
我附议
I second the motion.

95
00:03:47,090 --> 00:03:49,760
好 下周进行投票
Fine. Next week, you'll have your vote.

96
00:03:53,690 --> 00:03:55,690
- 现在咋办? - 分而治之
- What do we do now? - Divide and conquer.

97
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:58,650
只要琳达不在 说服他们就会简单些
When Linda's not around, it'll be easier to convince them.

98
00:03:58,670 --> 00:03:59,940
我们一个一个拿下他们
We'll go after them separately.

99
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,810
一个一个搞定
Ooh! Pick 'em off one by one.

100
00:04:01,830 --> 00:04:04,830
是的 只要我俩齐心 银河系唾手可得
Yes, and together, we shall rule the galaxy.

101
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:06,460
- 啥? - 没啥
- What? - What?

102
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,220
小伙子们 跑起来!
Keep moving, guys!

103
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,040
跑起来! 传球!
Keep it going! Pass the ball!

104
00:04:10,060 --> 00:04:12,080
干的不错 迪克踢得不错
Nice work, Dick. Way to get a piece of that ball.

105
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:13,700
你真棒
It's a great job.

106
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:16,530
我不懂 真心不懂
I'm confused. I'm very confused.

107
00:04:16,550 --> 00:04:19,170
看上去 迪克表现很糟
It would appear that Dick is not doing a great job.

108
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:21,840
实际上 他是队里最差的球员
In fact, I would say that he is the worst player on the team,

109
00:04:21,860 --> 00:04:24,490
但你仍说他做的很好
and yet you keep lying about his performance.

110
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:27,370
听着 杰西 做教练就是要积极强化
Listen, Jackie, coaching's about positive reinforcement.

111
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:30,490
好吧 说实话 这孩子绝对成不了贝克汉姆
Okay, let's face it, kid's never gonna be David Beckham.

112
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:32,830
我们本准备给他起这个名字的
We almost named him David Beckham.

113
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:34,810
我倒觉得 只要稍加训练
As a matter of fact, I think with some practice,

114
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:38,070
迪克就可以成为地球上最伟大的球员
Dick could be the greatest soccer player the world has ever seen.

115
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,080
实则不然
Yeah, not so much.

116
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:43,410
要是我 我就不会抱这么高的...期望
I would lower those expectations... a lot.

117
00:04:43,430 --> 00:04:46,840
也许以后 他会长得像大卫・贝克汉姆
Well, maybe he could at least grow up to look like David Beckham.

118
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:48,690
不太可能吧
Mm, nope.

119
00:04:48,710 --> 00:04:51,080
不过也许我们鼓励他 他会玩的很开心呢
But if we encourage him, he'll probably have a good time.

120
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:53,250
加油 小伙子们 跑起来 动起来
Come on, guys, keep it going! Move it along!

121
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:54,610
拦住球 迪克!
Get the ball, Dick!

122
00:04:57,310 --> 00:04:59,010
就是这样! 漂亮 迪克!
That's it! Way to go, Dick!

123
00:04:59,030 --> 00:05:01,280
小伙子 你这次都快碰到球了呢
You almost made contact that time, buddy!

124
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:04,280
谢谢 感觉好多了 教练
Thanks. Felt great, coach.

125
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,020
好吧 真心不是贝克汉姆的料
Yeah, not David Beckham.

126
00:05:07,350 --> 00:05:09,970
记住 你比那些女人强大 黛比・韦弗
Remember, you are stronger than these women, Debbie Weaver.

127
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:12,620
她们要么听你的话 要么领略你的怒火
They must do your bidding or feel your wrath.

128
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,320
噢 谢了 拉里 
Oh, thanks, Larry.

129
00:05:14,330 --> 00:05:17,060
有个男人在背后支持的感觉真好
You know, it's nice to have a man supporting me on this.

130
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,890
我牙上有口红吗?
Do I have lipstick on my teeth?

131
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,920
有 我还以为你是故意抹的
Yes, but I thought that was on purpose.

132
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,310
嗨 伊丽莎白
Hi... Elizabeth.

133
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:24,660
很抱歉来打扰你
I'm sorry to bother you at home,

134
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,230
不过我们想说你有没有个一两分钟
but we were wondering if you had a few minutes

135
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,950
来谈谈点心义卖的事
to talk about the bake sale.

136
00:05:27,970 --> 00:05:29,050
我真的不太关心这事儿
I really haven't thought much about it.

137
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:31,700
我一般跟着琳达投票 等我决定好会告知你的
I usually just vote with Linda, but I'll let you know.

138
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,530
伊丽莎白 黛比・韦弗为了见你
Elizabeth, Debbie Weaver has spent all morning

139
00:05:35,550 --> 00:05:37,660
花了一早上的时间给牙齿涂口红
putting lipstick on her teeth to come talk to you.

140
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,260
我恳请你听她说完
I insist you hear her out.

141
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:42,310
他对家教会超级上心的
He's very passionate about the P.T.A.

142
00:05:42,790 --> 00:05:44,140
好吧
Okay.

143
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,380
不过上次我投琳达反对票
But the last time I voted against Linda,

144
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,770
我女儿可是一整年没有玩伴
my daughter didn't have a playdate for, like, a year.

145
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,330
她又矮又胖 她需要尽可能多的朋友
She's kinda chunky. She needs all the friends she can get.

146
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:52,510
这正是整件事如此重要的原因
And that's why this is so important,

147
00:05:52,530 --> 00:05:54,700
- 因为家教会是为所有人服务的 - 所有人
- because the P.T.A. is about everyone. - Everyone.

148
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,020
不是一个人
Not just one person.

149
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,920
对 今天只是个饼干
Yes, today it's about cookies.

150
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:01,430
明天也许是禁止你的胖丫头上学校年鉴
Tomorrow it's banning your potbellied daughter from the yearbook.

151
00:06:01,450 --> 00:06:03,310
伊丽莎白 将心比心
Elizabeth, mother to mother,

152
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:05,770
我们不能让琳达得逞
we can't let Linda get away with this.

153
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:08,300
进来吧
Come in.

154
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:11,290
太棒了
Excellent.

155
00:06:16,330 --> 00:06:19,570
再说 姜饼干比巧克力蛋糕卡路里少多了
Plus gingerbread cookies have fewer calories than brownies.

156
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:22,650
我知道你喜欢给孩子吃健康食品
I know you like to feed your kids healthy foods.

157
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:25,100
我知道你有一个博客专门讲这个
I know you have a blog about it, yeah.

158
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,940
听着 特蕾西 我得去做饭了
Listen, Tracy, I gotta start making dinner.

159
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,360
我指着你投票了好吗
Can I count on your vote?

160
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:30,640
真的? 太好了 谢谢
Yeah? Great! Thanks!

161
00:06:35,170 --> 00:06:37,740
我滴个神啊 您这短裤
Oh, dear lord, those shorts.

162
00:06:38,260 --> 00:06:39,890
是啊 还挺合身的
Yeah, they still fit.

163
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,560
是吗?
Do they?

164
00:06:41,810 --> 00:06:44,160
- 训练如何? - 太棒了
- How was your practice? - It was awesome.

