00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:03,720
嘿 迪克 干嘛呢?
Hey, Dick, what are you doing?

343
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,700
我在练习 这样我就有机会归队了
I'm practicing so that I might return to the team

344
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,060
我妈也会对我另眼相看
and regain my mother's respect.

345
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:11,270
但目前看来 完全没戏
So far, it's been a total disaster.

346
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:14,280
其实有时候是父母太把体育当回事了
Well, you know, sometimes parents take sports a little too seriously.

347
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:16,200
事实上我觉得
And the truth is, I think this might be

348
00:16:16,220 --> 00:16:17,870
这件事的问题在于你妈 不是你
more about your mom than you.

349
00:16:17,890 --> 00:16:20,030
但不可否认的是
But you must admit, by all metrics,

350
00:16:20,050 --> 00:16:21,820
我的体育真的太弱了
I am a pretty bad athlete.

351
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:23,640
弱爆了 但这不意味着
Oh, the worst. But that doesn't mean

352
00:16:23,660 --> 00:16:25,400
你妈没有为你而骄傲
that your mother isn't proud of you.

353
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:28,350
我感觉她在你这么大的时候和你一样
I think you're a lot like she was at this age,

354
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:31,190
体育真的帮她建立了自信
and sports really helped her with her self-esteem.

355
00:16:31,210 --> 00:16:33,480
她希望你也可以这样
And she just wants that same thing for you.

356
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,430
但我又不缺自信
But I'm not lacking self-esteem.

357
00:16:35,450 --> 00:16:37,750
我为啥要没自信? 你看
Why would I be? I mean, look at me.

358
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:40,210
谁人能有这等姿色?
Who else do you think could pull off this look?

359
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:42,420
还真不是一般人
Wow, not many.

360
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,390
你是个好孩子 迪克・布特克斯
You're a good kid, Dick Butkus.

361
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:46,140
快去穿上队服
Why don't you go get your uniform on?

362
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:48,100
让你归队啦
We're gonna go get you back on that team.

363
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:54,800
二 四 六 八!
Two, four, six, eight!

364
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:57,850
二 四 六 八! 二 四 六 八!
Two, four, six, eight! Two, four, six, eight!

365
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,530
迪克?
Dick?

366
00:17:06,170 --> 00:17:08,050
不惜任何代价取得胜利
Win at all costs.

367
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:10,490
坚决果断 绝不手软
Be fierce. Take no prisoners.

368
00:17:10,860 --> 00:17:12,400
我一点儿都不想我儿子
I don't miss my son at all.

369
00:17:15,060 --> 00:17:17,280
姜饼人!
Gingerbread cookies!

370
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:19,280
点心义卖 美味小姜饼

371
00:17:18,690 --> 00:17:20,830
帮助球队买新队服
Help the soccer team buy new uniforms.

372
00:17:20,850 --> 00:17:22,410
很好吃哦
They're yummy.

373
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:25,680
吃起来比看起来美味
They can't taste worse than they look.

374
00:17:26,510 --> 00:17:28,800
不管怎么说我觉得我们还是赢了的
You know, in spite of everything, I think this was quite a victory.

375
00:17:28,820 --> 00:17:30,850
真的? 你这么觉得 拉里?
Do you? Do you, Larry?

376
00:17:31,170 --> 00:17:33,080
我们一块饼干都没卖出去
We've sold zero cookies.

377
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:35,130
所有家长们都和我们保持距离
Alienated the parents of all our kids' friends,

378
00:17:35,150 --> 00:17:36,220
把一个女人搞疯了
drove a woman crazy,

379
00:17:36,270 --> 00:17:37,610
还做了人类史上
and made the worst gingerbread cookies

380
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:40,070
最难吃的姜饼
in the history of mankind.

381
00:17:40,090 --> 00:17:42,360
哪来的胜利 拉里?
So, why? Why, Larry?

382
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:44,660
因为我本来觉得在艺术项目和老师评估方面
Well, because I actually thought you had some pretty good ideas

383
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:48,940
你是很有想法的
about arts programs and teacher evaluation.

384
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:53,360
如果有人问我 我会否认 但是
And if anyone ever asks, I shall deny it, but...

385
00:17:53,810 --> 00:17:55,550
如果我需要一个人类女士
If I had to have a human woman

386
00:17:55,570 --> 00:17:57,070
来指导我孩子的教育
guiding my children's education,

387
00:17:57,090 --> 00:17:59,940
我会非常希望是你 黛比・韦弗
I'd be very happy if it were you, Debbie Weaver.

388
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:02,220
你是个好女人
You are a good human woman.

389
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:07,958
拉里 你的话让我感动死了
That is actually a very sweet thing to say, Larry.

390
00:18:08,710 --> 00:18:11,540
- 别这么怪怪的 - 不 你才怪
- Please don't be weird. - No, you're weird.

391
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,940
- 好吧 是挺怪的 - 是的
- Okay, well, this is weird. - It is.

392
00:18:18,090 --> 00:18:19,610
上 上!
Go, go!

393
00:18:22,450 --> 00:18:23,900
你好 教练妈妈
Hello, coach mother.

394
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,390
你好 儿子
Hello, son.

395
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,810
马蒂 你来我的球场干啥
Marty, what are you doing on my field?

396
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:29,810
你得让迪克归队
You need to put Dick in the game.

397
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:30,970
不 不行
No, I can't.

398
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,450
别这样 杰西 他又不是你
Oh, come on, Jackie. This isn't you.

399
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:35,800
我知道你担心迪克的自尊心受挫
I know you're worried about Dick's self-esteem,

400
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:38,530
但没必要 迪克很强大的
but you don't have to be. Dick is a great kid!

401
00:18:38,550 --> 00:18:41,080
瞧瞧他 聪明 有同情心
Look at him. He's smart, he's compassionate.

402
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:42,180
还很可爱
Huh? He's cute.

403
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:45,240
等我学会了敲防弹门的笑话
And once I learn a couple of bulletproof "knock-knock" jokes,

404
00:18:45,260 --> 00:18:47,570
- 我就天下无敌了 - 瞧见没?
- I'll be the total package. - You see that?

405
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:50,330
我就没见过哪个大人有他这么自信
I mean, I don't know an adult who's that confident.

406
00:18:50,350 --> 00:18:52,130
我就是担心
I just worry.

407
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:55,410
孩子们总是对那些特殊的孩子很残酷
Kids can be so cruel to unique children.

408
00:18:55,430 --> 00:18:58,570
虽然你很不一般
Although you are really quite remarkable.

409
00:18:59,070 --> 00:18:59,830
好吧
Okay.

410
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:05,330
加油 伙计 穿上
Here you go, buddy. Put these on.

411
00:19:09,710 --> 00:19:11,490
你是个好教练 马蒂・韦弗
You are a good coach, Marty Weaver.

412
00:19:12,050 --> 00:19:13,820
- 还好啦 - 嗯
- I'm okay. - Mm.

413
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:21,550
漂亮 迪克!
Nice try, Dick!

414
00:19:22,390 --> 00:19:23,900
不是吧
No, it wasn't.

415
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:27,390
拉里・伯德! 能说点鼓励的话吗!
Larry Bird! Say something encouraging!

416
00:19:27,410 --> 00:19:29,440
- 好吧 - 我是认真的
- Fine. - Honestly.

417
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,130
- 头发很飘逸啊 儿啊 - 是的呢!
- Your hair looks great, son! - Yes!

418
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:33,430
从你这遗传的 
He gets that from you.

419
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,140
谢谢 是从我这遗传的
 - Thank you. Yes, he does.

420
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,320
- 神啊 他太糟了 - 我知道
- Oh, God, he's terrible. - I know.

421
00:19:45,510 --> 00:19:46,520
嘿
Hey.

422
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:47,720
我能买块饼干么?
Can I buy a cookie?

423
00:19:47,780 --> 00:19:50,540
别了吧 除非你想品尝失败的滋味
I wouldn't. Unless you like the taste of failure.

424
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:53,150
所以说我们该一起干活的
You know, this is why we should do this stuff together,

425
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:54,850
因为我觉着我们配合的不错的
because I think we make a pretty good team.

426
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:57,130
不是吧 我们配合是超好的
Oh, come on. We make a great team.

427
00:19:58,330 --> 00:20:00,880
有人说我是很棒的教练
You know, I've been told that I'm a fantastic coach.

428
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:03,730
有人说我是个好女人
Well, I've been told that I'm a pretty good human woman, so...

429
00:20:05,140 --> 00:20:06,120
你怎么办到的? 
How did you do it?

430
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:07,500
嗨 琳达 什么怎么办到?
Hi, Linda. Do what?

431
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:09,290
姜饼人 它是活的!
The gingerbread man... it was alive!

432
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:11,730
我不知道是怎么办到的 但它是活的
I don't know how, but it was alive.

433
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:14,470
我觉得就是突然然间发生太多事 你没适应好
You know, I think you're just stressed out from the drama of everything.

434
00:20:14,490 --> 00:20:16,950
根本没有活的姜饼人 琳达
There's no such thing as a living gingerbread man, Linda.

435
00:20:16,970 --> 00:20:18,870
真的?
Oh. Really?

436
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:21,340
把球捡回来 迪克!
Get the ball, Dick!

437
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:24,130
我跑的够快了!
I'm running as fast as I can!

438
00:20:30,710 --> 00:20:32,040
她好活泼哦
She's a little jumpy.

439
00:20:32,060 --> 00:20:34,120
是的 有点敏感
Yeah, a little high-strung.


